properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued January 30 at 1:46AM MST until January 30 at 8:00PM MST by NWS Rapid City SD
properties.description:
* WHAT...Northwest winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 55 mph
expected. The strongest winds are expected over far northwest
South Dakota this afternoon.

* WHERE...Portions of northwestern and southwestern South Dakota.

* WHEN...From noon today to 8 PM MST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Sudden wind gusts can cause drivers to lose control,
especially in lightweight or high profile vehicles. Strong
winds can cause blowing dust, reduced visibility, and flying
debris.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Patchy blowing snow will be possible in
portions of northwest South Dakota, mainly this afternoon,
leading to reduced visibility at times.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM NOON TODAY TO 8 PM MST THIS EVENING
